\subtree{ \title{Summary}

\p{This PR introduces the basic notions for working with categories in
  STT. We define reflective subuniverses of [simplicial
  types](stt-00AC), [precategories](stt-00AI) and
  [groupoids](stt-00B6). We also define [covariant families](stt-00AY)
  and [left fibrations](stt-00AV).}


\p{We introduce a module that when instantiated at a particular type
  axiomatises the [root type former](stt-00AF) showing that
  exponentiation at that type has an [amazing right
  adjoint](stt-00AA). Using this we define #{\mathcal{S}}, the
  [category of groupoids](stt-00AS). Many facts about #{\mathcal{S}} are yet
  to be formalised, including that the [directed univalence
  map](stt-00AT) is an equivalence and that #{\mathcal{S}} itself is
  actually a category.}  }

