\p{This PR feels somewhat momentous; the [first trees](stt-0004) in
this forest were created in February, 2025, and now around 10 months
later we have finally gotten to the point where we are formalising some
synthetic category theory. The time put into developing the rest of the
library feels like it has payed off in these changes, especially all
the work on [reflective subuniverses](stt-007S). It was a relatively
painless process to bootstrap the simplicial part of the library, and
I am optimistic about working with STT without the strictness introduced
in a system like [the rzk proof assistant](rzk).}

\subtree{
\title{Future plans}
\ul{
\li{We introduced a new layout for writing long chains of
equality/equivalence proofs (see for example \ref{stt-00AW}). It would
be nice to rewrite some particularly ugly/hard to read proofs to use
this layout style.}

\li{We got some ways through trying to prove
equivalent span diagrams give equivalent pushouts - but ended up not
needing this proof and so it didn't get fully formalised. (See [this
issue](https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/issues/37)
for more details) }
  \li{In general, it's time to formalise more basic category theory,
 for example: lax pullbacks/pushouts, limits and adjunctions}
